# keidai-ui component library

`@keidai/ui` (`packages/ui`) is the design system. **Reach for it first** when building UI in `apps/keidai-ui`. Check `packages/ui/src/index.ts` for available exports; see `packages/ui/README.md` for workflow and patterns.

## Import from `@keidai/ui`

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
import { Card, CardContent, Table, TableRow, Button, Badge } from "@keidai/ui";

// ❌ BAD — hand-rolled equivalents
<div className="rounded-xl border border-border bg-card">…</div>
<table>…</table>
<button type="button">…</button>
```

Use `cn` from `@keidai/ui` for conditional classes. Use design tokens (`bg-card`, `border-border`, `text-muted-foreground`) — not one-off styling that duplicates primitives.

## Component map

| UI need | Use |
|---------|-----|
| Bordered panel / empty state / summary tile | `Card`, `CardHeader`, `CardTitle`, `CardDescription`, `CardContent`, `CardFooter` |
| Tabular data | `Table`, `TableHeader`, `TableBody`, `TableRow`, `TableHead`, `TableCell` |
| Modal / multi-step flow | `Dialog`, `DialogContent`, `DialogHeader`, `DialogTitle`, `DialogDescription`, `DialogFooter`, `DialogClose` |
| Side panel | `Sheet` + subcomponents |
| Actions | `Button` |
| Status / tags / chips | `Badge` |
| Dividers | `Separator` |
| Hover detail | `Tooltip` + `TooltipProvider` |

