## Missing primitive?

If no `@keidai/ui` export fits (e.g. Alert, Avatar, Collapsible, DropdownMenu), **add it to `packages/ui` via shadcn CLI and export from `index.ts`** — do not inline a one-off in keidai-ui.

```bash
cd packages/ui && npx shadcn@latest add alert
```

Then export the new component from `packages/ui/src/index.ts` and use it in keidai-ui.

## Allowed raw markup

Layout wrappers (`div`, `span`, `p`), icons (`lucide-react`), and domain-specific composites (e.g. `OwnerAvatar` until `Avatar` lands in `@keidai/ui`) are fine. Do not use raw HTML for primitives that already exist in the library.
